The paper proposes a method for learning spatiotemporal representation in video recognition tasks using a parameter-free plug-in component that efficiently reallocates the inputs of 2D convolution so that its receptive field can be extended to the temporal dimension. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
